What you need to know:  In a statement, FIDAL said that Italian Jacobs underwent tests on Wednesday which assessed his recovery from the muscle injury diagnosed in MayJacobs, a shock winner of the 100 metres in the Tokyo Olympics last year, has only raced at the distance twice since his stunning win in Japan, both underwhelming runs at a meeting in Savona last monthThe 27-year old said at last week's Diamond League event in Rome that he was hoping to compete in "one or two" events before the worlds